Product name: Vintage Chinese Porcelain Vase, Blue and White Porcelain Bottle Vase, Squat Form Vase, Chinese Republic Period Vase, Painted Vase
Description:
This listing is for a vintage Chinese porcelain vase. 
This blue and white porcelain vase is decorated with an image of a figure on a bridge.  The vase is a squat form, or bottle shape.
The vase's decoration is very nicely painted but one end of the design has been damaged in production.  The blue underglaze at the far left hand side of the design has been lost.  I've provided a photograph above.  
I believe the vase is of the Chinese republic period.
Apart from the fault to the blue decoration noted above, there are the following areas of damage to note:
*  There is a crack to the glaze at the rim of the vase (photograph provided).  The damage doesn't seem to extend through to the porcelain, it appears to be in the glaze only.
*  There are a number of pin holes on the outer surface of the glaze.
*  The rim at the base has a number of small chips.
The vase is 14cm tall (5.5 inches), and approximately 10cm across at its widest point (4 inches).
If you need any further information or photos, please do send me convo. I’m more than happy to answer questions or send further images
